  Here is my free advice on training points.  Worth everything it costs.   )<br>
<br>
  Do not put training points into skills that will improve through your use.  Just hit the sense heading button whenever you are sitting waiting for a boat or any other down time and the skill will improve after you put one original point into it.  Other skills will go up with use like offense, defense, meditate, conj, abj, and so on. <br>
<br>
  Soon you will encounter the need to develop research skill to get spells that are research only.  Or you will want to start tradeskills that take time and money to master.  I recommend saving training points for those purposes mostly. <br>
<br>
  For research, wait as long as you possibly can before putting your first point into research.  I forget the formula, but it is level based.  If you put your first point in research at level 2 for instance, your research skill will start at 3 or something.  Then you'll have to train it up from there.  If you put your first point in at level 20, your research skill will start at like 21 or something.  You save all the skillups from like 3 to 21.  So wait as long as you can.  <br>
<br>
  Save up your training points and use them to max your research skill at each level.  Then making your researched spells is trivial.  You never have to do the stupid research training.  This won't take all your training points, and you can also use some for tradeskills.   If you were very lucky, you picked Tunare for your diety and can use the high elf cultural armor.  So blacksmithing is a good tradeskill along with jewel craft. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/03 2:19:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=56>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaPhoto2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Training points</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you were very lucky, you picked Tunare for your diety and can use the high elf cultural armor.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
