  Don't feel bad.  I'm a high elf and I picked Karana.  Had no idea it made any difference.  Oh well, it kept me out of the blacksmithing time sink.   As far as tradeskills go, I highly recommend working on your tailoring as you go along.  I did the 7 prayer shawl quests in Thurgadin and that was probably the best quest I've done in EQ.  The quest is a lot of fun, and end item is very nice.  There is an 8th shawl now, but it takes a lot of help to get.  You will need most of your tradeskills in the 160 range to finish the 7th shawl.  Tailoring is probably the toughest and most important for that quest.  If you work on tailoring a little at a time, you will get it up without it being such a struggle.<br>
