   EQ Traders on the internet is the best site I know for tradeskill information.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/03 2:58:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Training points</span><hr size=1> It is not quite correct that all skills improve, just because you use them. If you haven't trained in swimming and start to swimm (e.g. because you fell in) you will get skillups. I don't think you will get skillups in sense heading if you haven't put one point into it, but one point is enough. The skill is really bad for a lot of levels and it isn't unusual that you have to hit the button many times before you get a reading.<br>
<br>
Regarding points. When you start a charcter you have 5 points to spend and for each level you gain you get 5 new. Unless you especially want to achieve something, i can't advise putting more than one point in a skill. There is also a point in saving points, because you later more easily can boost a skill. Currently at lv 59 i have 40 unused points and quite frankly no idea what to use them for. All tradeskills are so high that I can't advance in them at a trainer (you can't train a tradeskill above 20 at the trainer and further advancements come from using the skill). I actually had a lot more, but dumped a lot of point in some mele skills just for the heck of it.<br>
<br>
Sense heading is very usefull, but not all that hard to keep maxed from use. <br>
<br>
Jewelry is more or less a wasted skill. The reason for this is simple. As a magician you can combine metals and gems to jewelry, however the finished product isn't magic, it is just a trinket. In order for it to be magic and give stats like int, the metal needs to be enchanted and that is a thing only an enchanter can do. It also takes a high skill to make anything which is very usefull. Jewelry is a skill that is easy, but expencive to raise. You can ask enchanters to enchant metals for you, BUT expect to have to pay for it. <br>
<br>
Many magicians like to do tailoring, because the pet is an excelent farming tool, however at high levels that too becomes difficult because nearly nothing can be bourght from a shop.<br>
<br>
As for how to use the patterns, the one that gives the quest usually also gives some instructions to how to do it.<br>
<br>
